The paper discusses a software product line (SPL) and proposes an approach to reverse engineer the architecture of a set of product variants. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on managing variability, which is a key aspect of Product Line Engineering (cs.PL). The paper also mentions analyzing the business domain, which is related to Software Design (cs.SD). The use of Formal Concept Analysis (FCA) suggests that the paper may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an approach that involves analyzing and identifying dependencies, which is a common theme in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
